  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobile Meter Reading</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobile Water Management (MWM) enables the monitoring of water variables with the smartphone of water managers and citizens. Different parameters can be monitored on location, such as water level, groundwater level, rainfall water quality and the meter readings of drinking water facilities within houses. All measurements come together in an open web-based GIS database that is accessible to everyone and everywhere. In this demonstration project MWMs mobile water meters will be used in combination with Hydrologics HydroNET platform to demonstrate in Johannesburg the possibility of using a smartphone in a smart, low cost, fraud-free way to read meter readings. This may open up the market in South Africa for MWM to market this method of water metering.Johannesburg Water is the local partner that will test the mobile water meters at a part of its customers. Johannesburg Water has a problem surrounding the invoicing of water consumption. Many consumers are currently questioning the use of water they are being billed, which in turn leads to a breach of trust between consumer and Johannesburg Water. By deploying the mobile water measurements of MWM, Johannesburg hopes to find a more accurate method for invoicing water use, which will be more easily accepted by its customers. Johannesburg also wants to investigate water how this type of data on a visual platform enables itpro actively monitor the water usage. Lastly, Johannesburg Water wants to better understand how this data on an accessible visual platform can bring about a change in behavior among its customers (eg sparing behavior at the customer by comparing).</narrative>
  </description>
